docs.lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — Two American service members were killed and two others were wounded in a roadside bomb explosion in southern Afghanistan on Saturday, the United States military command in Afghanistan said in a statement. They were the first American military fatalities in Afghanistan this year.

docs.abstract: The former Nissan executive remains in Tokyo, awaiting a trial on criminal charges that he helped Mr. Ghosn hide his compensation.
docs.snippet: The former Nissan executive remains in Tokyo, awaiting a trial on criminal charges that he helped Mr. Ghosn hide his compensation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Every weekday morning, Greg Kelly, the former Nissan executive accused of helping Carlos Ghosn hide his compensation from the Japanese authorities, makes his way to his lawyer’s office in Tokyo to chip away at a monumental task: reviewing close to one billion pages of documents.

docs.abstract: She attributed her move to creative differences. “In my opinion,” she said, “there is more work to be done on the film to illuminate the full scope” of the women’s allegations of sexual abuse.

docs.lead_paragraph: Oprah Winfrey said on Friday that she was cutting ties with a documentary centered on women who have accused the music mogul Russell Simmons of sexual misconduct. The untitled film, scheduled to have its premiere this month at the Sundance Film Festival, focuses primarily on the executive Drew Dixon, who accused Mr. Simmons of raping her, an accusation Mr. Simmons has repeatedly denied.

headline.main: Oprah Winfrey Pulls Out of Documentary on the Music Mogul Russell Simmons
headline.print_headline: Oprah Walks Away From Documentary on Music Mogul Allegations
